## ⚠ This is source-available software, not open source

The source code can be read, but this is **not** an open-source licence and Sightline must not be
described as open source. It does not meet the Open Source Definition: it restricts redistribution and
commercial exploitation of the source, which a genuine open-source licence may not do.

Publishing the source on a public repository does not place it in the public domain and does not waive
copyright. All rights not expressly granted below are reserved.

### In plain English

| You may | You may not |
|---|---|
| Read, study and review the source | Redistribute the source or a build of it |
| Build it yourself to evaluate or verify it | Publish a modified version |
| **Use the Software at work, commercially** | Sell, sublicense or rent the Software or its source |
| Submit improvements back | Use the source to build a competing product |
| Fork on GitHub, via GitHub's own features | Run it as a hosted or managed service for others |

This table is a summary for convenience. Where it and the clauses below differ, the clauses govern.

